S IWASJU50C1ATJONJ\ntttt For Political AnnouncamanU.\nKor Precinct and City Office.. $5.00\nFor County Offices 10.00\nFor State and District Offices.. 16.00\n'or Calls, per line. .10\n,ror Cards, per line .10\nFor all publications in the inter\nest of individuals or expres\nsion of individual views, per\nline 10\nObituaries, per line .05\nPyramiding Wealth.\nmay come a time wnen pyra\nmided wealth becomes the red\nrag of destructive revolution.\nWhen governments become\nblind the people are forced to\ndp their own seeing, and under\nstress of great provocation\nthey are too often inclined to\n\"see red.\"\nIt is time for all advocates\nof the s(i ti a re deal to sound a\nwarning call.\nWashington should sit up\nand take heed.\nPeople wholovc their coun\ntry do not care to see it come\nto grief through the cupidity\nof money maniacs.\nAs The Editor Sees It.\nLooking forward at the be\ngininng of a new year is a\ncommon occurance in all coun\ntries, and as we pursue the age\nold custom wo cannot take\nnote of the contrast between\nconditions in our own country\nand those beyond the seas.\nIn our land we have a solid,\nsubstantial government, found\ned upon the guarantee of life,\nliberty and the pursuit of hap\npiness. I Or,f ilinrj Ifitura rind ntn-\nA New York dispatch re\ncently stated that families in\nthe United States control more\nthan $100,000,000 each; one\nhundred families control over\n$50,000,000 each, and Ave\nhundred families control more\nthan $10,000,000 each.'\nJohn D. Kockfeller's is now h bcen kjcke(, from\nsaid to be between $11,000,-;thc. thronc3 governments\n000,000 and $4,000,000,000. hnve bcen drivcn from power\nIt is the hoarding (if such lnw aml ordcr huve buc, sub.\nvast fortunes as these into teiStUute(, by choas, and hatred\nhands of a few that has made am, HU8I)jclon iurk in the\nRussia bolshevistic and driven hcnrts of the many\nits ruling class to pauper and: Hcru we ,mvo education, re-\ndeath. fitiiimimt liiMilth u'ftiillli nrno.\nfor the future.\npeace with our\nneighbors ami are not looking\nfor or dodging trouble.\nBut on the other side all is\ndiiferent.\nPractically every foreign\ngovernment is setting on the\nlid of a volcano. Open dis\ncord exists everywhere.\nThousands who have lived\nin luxury in former years are\nIt is the wedge that has di- ,lcrity aml hope\nvided the wealthy claas from aru a )eH\nthe great mass or the people\nthroughout the countries of\nEurope, and has created wide\nspread dissatisfaction that has\nbrought on wars and toppled\njptjl iuojj tuoaoiluio puu 8ttut?t\nthrones.\nOnly the blind and the fool\nish will continue to consider\nthis country immune.\nIt is difficult to induce peo\nple to believe that such gigan\ntic fortunes can be accumulat\ned by honest methods in the\napace of a few years, and dis\nhonesty Is the rock upon which\ngovernment! and individuals\nsooner or later come to grief.\nThe pyramiding of wealth is\nthe most dangerous disease\nwith which our country is af\nflicted today.\nIt indicates the existence\noC protUeering combinations\nwhich are inimical to the wel\nfare of the republic.\nOfficial complaisance will\nnot ease the tension, and\ndoling out a- few thousands\nwill not wash away the sins clothing\nof its accumulation. Destitution and\nShaking a red rag in the everywhere. -face\nof a bull maddens the ani-j Prosperity-la- nowhere,\nma! and starts it on a wild Truly, it hi good to live in\nnow penniless, many of them\nuncertain as to the source from\nwhence tho next meal is to\ncome.\nThose who have seized the\nwealth of the countries in the\noverthrow of government are\nin the main ignorant as to how\nto turn it to account, or are\nwasting the substance in riot\nous living.\nCommerce is stagnant and\nfunds are lacking for its resus\ncitation. Millions are on the verge of\nstarvation or are in the actual\nthroes of dissolution.\nChildren are perishig in the\ncold through lack of proper\nwant arc\ndepression and are now on the\nup grade. Only the rankest\nkind of pessimism can hold us\nback.\nAnd who wants to be a pes\nsimist when every human in\nstinct spurs us on to optimism?\nLet's demonstrate our faith\nin the return of prosperity by\nrecognizing the fact that it is\nhere and by doing our share\ntoward its maintaincnance in\nthis community.\nLet the watchword be pro\nduction, wisdom in spending,\nand employment of systematic\ncourse of saving.\nA proportionate amount of\nthe prosperity of the country\nbelongs to the people of this\ncommunity.\nLet's get all we can and\nkeep all we get.\nOther communities will be\ndoing the same.\nPampered Brains.\nWe all admire a smart\nyoung man, but we do not ad\nmire him when he becomes\n\"too smart.\"\nThat is the trouble with\nmany young men.\nThey are endowed by nature\nwith more than the average al\nlotment of brains, but they\nlack the poise and judgment\nnecessary to keep them under\ncontrol.\nThis deficiency, however, is\nnot so much their fault as it\nis the fault of their parents.\nWhen a baby shows indica\ntions of being quick wittcd too\nmany parents immediately be\ngin to humor il and spoil it.\ny-iusieau oi maintaining a\ngentle but firm control over\nthe child they give in to us\nwhims and encourage it in\nwilfulness.\nIt grows up with the idea\nfirmly implanted in its mind\nthat it must have its own way\nin everything.\nIf it makes a pert remark\nand is not corrected that re\nmark calls for others in kind,\nand this leads naturally to the\nspirit of \"smartness\" which we\nso greatly deplore in many\nyoung fellows just entering\nman's estate.\nHrains in the cradle requires\nnursing.\nPampering only converts\nthem into the egotism of ma\nturity.\nUndressed Kid.\n\"The bride wait dressed in filmy\nwhite, looking Ilka n summer cloud.\nThe groom was in conventional\nblack; he wore white shirt, white\nvest and white gloves, which he re\nmoved during the ccrcmony,\"Vcr\nmont Union Journal.\nEvery good citizen doea his part.\nHave you dono yours?\nsure that